== English ==
=== Etymology ===
Latin "it does not follow"

=== Noun ===
# (''Logic'') An invalid argument; one in which the [[conclusion]] cannot be logically [[deduce]]d from the [[premise]]s. Literally in Latin "does not follow".
#: ''The argument "All ravens are black; this object is black; therefore this obejct is a raven" is a non sequitur''
# Any abrupt and inexplicable transition or occurrence
#: ''Having a costumed superhero abduct the vicar was an utter non sequitur''

